
[1]evil-minded

   EVIL-MINDED, a. [evil and mind.] Having evil dispositions or
   intentions; disposed to mischief or sin; malicious; malignant; wicked.
   Slanderous reports are propagated by evil-minded persons. [This word is
   in common use.]
